# Build Bible V2 — Chapter 3 (Next.js & TypeScript)

Spec: `docs/05_BUILD_BIBLE_V2_CHAPTER_03_NEXT_TYPESCRIPT.md`

## Next.js

- Prefer Server Components; `"use client"` only when technically required.
- Keep App Router files consistent (`page` / `layout` / `loading` / `error` / `not-found` / `route`).
- Fetch on the server when possible; avoid duplicate client fetches and waterfalls.
- Thin API routes; delegate to `src/lib/**`.

## TypeScript

- Strict typing; no `any`, `@ts-ignore`, or `@ts-nocheck` unless unavoidable.
- Avoid unjustified `as never` / unsafe assertions.
- Exported functions and services use explicit types.
- Preserve API and DB contracts.

## Boundaries & security

- Never import `server-only`, `@/lib/supabase/server`, or `@/lib/supabase/admin` into Client Components.
- No secrets in client bundles.

## Preserve

- Features, RBAC, RLS, Paddle billing, authentication/authorization behaviour.
- Never reintroduce Stripe.

## This chapter

- Do not commit, push, or deploy from Chapter 3 work.
